            "body": "<p>You can use a BufferedReader, FileReader or Scanner object to read txt files in Java. It depends on which you'd like to use for it's functions.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can use them to iterate trough lines in the txt file and you can put that read content in a String. Then you can assign that stringvalue to your objectvariables.<\/p>\n\n<p>A quick google brought me to this website which explains the methods complete with code examples: <a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/different-ways-reading-text-file-java/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/different-ways-reading-text-file-java/<\/a><\/p>\n",
